30/30 pass, zero races. Here's what Stage 4 adds and why:

**The non-obvious fix — outer loop refactor**

The STP skip reveals a latent infinite-loop: when every order at the best price level belongs to the same owner, `matchLevel` skips them all, `lvl.queue.Len() != 0`, so the old loop never advanced `ob.bestAsk`. The fix decouples the sweep cursor from the book cursor. [match.go:16-27](engine/match.go#L16-L27):

```go
for cur := ob.bestAsk; cur != 0 && cur <= int(o.Price) && o.Remaining > 0; {
    lvl := ob.asks[cur]
    ob.matchLevel(o, lvl)
    nextCur := ob.nextBestAsk(cur)          // always advances past cur
    if lvl.queue.Len() == 0 {
        ob.asks[cur] = nil
        if ob.bestAsk == cur {
            ob.bestAsk = nextCur            // book cursor only moves on actual empty
        }
    }
    cur = nextCur                           // sweep cursor always moves
}
```

**The STP skip** — [match.go:65-68](engine/match.go#L65-L68):

```go
if resting.OwnerID == incoming.OwnerID {
    e = e.Next()
    continue
}
```

No fill, no `TotalVolume` change, no removal, no status update.

